column12: SYSTEM, APPARATUS AND METHOD FOR STORAGE AND TRANSPORTATION OF PERSONAL HEALTH RECORDS
column13: A system (100) and process for storing, managing, transporting and communicating personal health and medical information. According to a representative embodiment, the present invention includes a non-volatile memory device (218), such as a USB Flash Memory, which is easily portable by the user and which can be made secure. The present invention can be configured to auto launch emergency information and can further include data-encryption and/or password protection of user-directed health and medical information, interfaces (214,216) with information technology artifacts, network (102) and Internet capabilities, and program code storage.
